ëA river rat is inured to dangers presented by disease-carrying parasites, poisonous fish, and other toxic river denizens. At 3rd level, a river rat gains a +1 bonus on saving throws against disease and poison effects. This bonus increases by 1 every 3 levels thereafter, to a maximum bonus of +6 at 18th level.
This replaces trap sense.
Rogue Talents: The following rogue talents complement the river rat archetype: camouflage, hold breath, rogue crawl, stand up, strong stroke, survivalist.ª.
